public static class ArithmeticExpansion.Operator extends Object implements Comparable<ArithmeticExpansion.Operator>, Serializable, Unique
An arithmetic expansion operator is a singleton object that specifies how an arithmetic operator should be applied to a series of numeric expressions.

    • expand

      public Expression expand(Variable variable, Expression argument)
      Returns a numeric expression which is logically equivalent to an arithmetic expansion with this operator but which does not contain this operator or variable.
      Parameters:
      variable - a variable which appears in the expression and for which every possible value will be substituted
      argument - a numeric expression which contains the variable and which will be used to create the series of numeric expressions
      Returns:
      a numeric expression logically equivalent to an arithmetic expansion using this operator but which does not contain this operator or the variable
